               <msContents>
                  <summary>On the recto is a document of uncertain content.  On the verso is the phrase, "apodesmos sun[teleion," indicating that the papyrus was used as wrapping.</summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">Fragmentary papyrus; placement of pieces uncertain; two margins: top (0.1-0.6 cm) and right (ca. 2 cm)</note>
                     <note type="general">Papyrus found wrapped around 6-10</note>
                     <note type="general">Recto and verso in different hands, with writing on both sides along the fibers</note>
                     <note type="general">For a reproduction, see Plate XXVI</note>
                     <note type="general">Written in same provincial year as P.Petra I 7; for the date, see entry in HGV</note>
